article.headline: George Mason 65, William & Mary 46
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Tony Skinn scored 19 points and Will Thomas had 14 Thursday night, leading George Mason to a 65-46 victory against William & Mary. The Patriots (11-4, 5-1 Colonial Athletic Association) led 29-20 at halftime and shot better than 63 percent in the second half, including 6-for-7 on 3-pointers. Skinn was 3-for-4 from behind the arc in the game, and Lamar Butler, who scored 10, was 3-for-6. The Tribe (5-9, 0-5) was led by Taylor Mokris with 13 points. Taylor made 6 of 7 from the field, while the rest of the team made 12 of 44, just 27 percent.
